arb4j source package
====================

Upstream
--------
arb4j is maintained at https://github.com/crowlogic/arb4j by Stephen
Crowley <stephencrowley214@gmail.com>.  The Debian source package is the
unmodified upstream tree plus the debian/ directory.

Build system
------------
arb4j is a Maven project.  The Debian build invokes Maven in offline
mode (`mvn -o`) against the local repository populated by the upstream
`pom.xml`.  Two `maven-dependency-plugin` executions are bound to the
`prepare-package` phase:

  build-classpath-debian
      writes build/class.path.debian, one runtime jar per line, each
      prefixed with /usr/share/arb4j/lib/.

  copy-dependencies-debian
      copies every runtime jar into build/dependency/.

debian/rules then installs:

  • the thin arb4j jar to /usr/share/java/arb4j-<version>.jar with an
    arb4j.jar symlink;
  • build/dependency/*.jar to /usr/share/arb4j/lib/;
  • build/class.path.debian to /usr/share/arb4j/class.path;
  • the .so entries inside lib/javafx-*-linux.jar and
    lib/j2v8_linux_*.jar to /usr/lib/jni/.

The launcher in debian/env.sh.in composes ARB4J_CLASSPATH from the
thin jar followed by the colon-joined contents of class.path.

Native classifier jars
----------------------
The four JavaFX `*-linux.jar` artifacts and `j2v8_linux_x86_64-*.jar`
are the only jars that contain platform-native `.so` payloads.  Every
other jar in /usr/share/arb4j/lib/ is pure Java bytecode.

Repacking
---------
No upstream repacking is performed.  `dpkg-source -x` produces a tree
that builds with `dpkg-buildpackage -b -us -uc` directly, given a
populated local Maven repository for the declared dependencies.

